%e A036355 For example, T(4,2) = 14 and there are 14 lattice paths from (0,0) to (4-2,2) = (2,2) using steps (1,0),(2,0),(0,1),(0,2). - _Greg Dresden_, Aug 25 2020
%t A036355 nmax = 11; t[n_, m_] := t[n, m] = tp[n-1, m-1] + tp[n-2, m-2] + tp[n-1, m] + tp[n-2, m]; tp[n_, m_] /; 0 <= m <= n && n >= 0 := t[n, m]; tp[n_, m_] = 0; t[0, 0] = 1; Flatten[ Table[t[n, m], {n, 0, nmax}, {m, 0, n}]] (* _Jean-Fran√ßois Alcover_, Nov 09 2011, after formula *)
